6.Galdriels Glade<br>
7.<a href="javascript:card_browser(233)">Anduin Wilderland</a><br>
8.<a href="javascript:card_browser(235)">Anduin Banks</a><br>
9.Tol Brandier<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> THIS IS PRE ELF LORDS BUT ELF LORDS HAS NOT REALLY MADE THE GAME THAT MUCH DIFFERENT so plz read strat. (^_^)<br>
First off this is the deck that has got me to number 1 in Australia, with a ranking of 1940 and 21 in the world at that. Secondly this deck as you probably already know won me the New South Wales Territorials. The decks current tournament run is 57-6 and the 5 games that I lost were games that I played in an early couple of tournaments where I wasn&#8217;t really confident in the deck and one game at the NSW Territorial, I now know how to play against all deck types with it and that is why I have gone so well. <br>
<br>
This deck usually starts legolas and Sam and mostly bids five you can go to six but it is hazardous. I bid five because u take 3 off with Sam and then add 1 burden to get aragorn so I end up with three and I can always get another one off w/ pippin and h/appetite. Even though 3 is vulnerable to nazgul sword it is unlikely they will get one in their opening hand and I will remove the other burdens if I get sam on the next sanctuary or I get pippin. I don&#8217;t go 4 because toldea and 5 is asking to be Enquead. Any less than 5 bid you cant really expect to win the bid. If you lose the bid and then they start the greed dragon inn, you should start gimli and legolas because you should get aragorn with 4 in a 60 card deck. If they start anything else then just stick with the plan and you should get aragorn or gandalf as you have 2 gandalf & a wizard is never late.<br>
<br>
Now the main idea of the fellowship is that you can drop everything out of your hand except: sleep, No mere ranger, and servant and in some circumstances Hobbit/a if your hobbits are not injured. I did have ARV but it is now errated but you can put it in for servant or N.M.R if you are wary of the cave troll. <br>
So by dropping all of the cards in your hand you then get two advantages of pumping up your fellowship and you also get your minions to beat down your opponent which creates a vicious cycle of you dropping f/p and getting shadow, then dropping the shadow to get f/p, etc.<br>
<br>
This is just a reason list for certain cards in the deck.<br>
<br>
Hobbit Appetite-<br>
This is good late game for the run to nine when merry is not able to use his ability and you use it to heal him which equal fellowship beats. It is also good for anti-direct damages because when the bowmen and under the watching eye come out then you take the wounds on pippin and frodo and just heal them with hobbit appetite and negate the direct damage. It is also good early game to get more burdens off with sam.<br>
<br>
<br>
No mere ranger, wizard staff, merry, servant- <br>
These are just essential cards to help you against uruk. When they pull out savagery you can use any of these and kill the uruk + they have wasted a savagery.<br>
<br>
Dreary + Sleep = No conditions which = moria tends to die without conditions<br>
<br>
Spies of Saruman-<br>
You may want to drop a spies as aimed archery doesn&#8217;t seem to be as common these days but I still keep 2 as a safety precaution.<br>
<br>
Lurtz x3-<br>
Besides being the beefiest uruk that wrecks fellowship, Lurtz is the best way around hobtookoke. This fellowship can usually keep up with the opponent if they go first so when they get to the bridge you don&#8217;t want to waste your uruk being stealthed you want to stop them dead. So you can get lurtz down as the bridge gives off so much twilight and Lurtz is usually fierce so they use their stealths and if they move on they still have to contend with lurtz and nobody in their right mind would move on if a fierce lurtz would come back again.<br>
<br>
Lurtz&#8217;s battle cry-<br>
It is either this or sarumans power if you are worried about ranger decks use power. This is a good card as it allows you to kill off those annoying companions with 3 vitality that don&#8217;t get overwhelmed.<br>
<br>
Savagery to match their numbers-<br>
Need I say more!<br>
<br>
<br>
This deck plays well against all deck types and I would suggest giving it a go. The only small trouble it has against decks is when they also play uruk-hai but you may want to add another armor for that. You might want to add other stuff from elf lords like saruman but I still think it would okay without it. If you do decide to play the deck I hope you have as much success as did.<br>
<br>
!  <br>
<br>
